# Issue Title

Within a downstream `microsoft/dotnet:2.0-sdk` or `microsoft/dotnet:2.0-runtime` Docker image, any calls to `ZipArchive.CreateEntryFromFile` or `FileStream.CopyTo(GZipStream)` result in a segmentation fault.

# General

 - Downstream image, built from `microsoft/dotnet` Docker hub image(s)
 - .NET Core version 2.0 & 2.1.101

```csharp
                using (FileStream fs = new FileStream(archiveFilePath, FileMode.Create)) {
                using (ZipArchive archive = new ZipArchive(fs, ZipArchiveMode.Update)) {
                    archive.CreateEntryFromFile(f, f);
                }
```

Running outside of a container, and everything works as expected, it's only when running within a container. The Core 2.0 failures were run with older `microsoft/dotnet` images, while the 2.1.101 were run with the images that exist today.

